                <expan><abbr>Iumma</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> Exobni <expan><abbr>fil</abbr><ex>io</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>cive <note>sic</note> Mediomatrico <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>m</ex></expan> C Atuns <lb n="4"/>Bunnae <expan><abbr>filia</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>iugi</abbr></expan> eius <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>m</ex></expan> LXXX <expan><abbr>Dome</abbr><ex cert="low">tius</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/>Iustus filius et <expan><ex>h</ex><abbr>ere</abbr><ex>s</ex></expan> par<lb break="no" n="7"/>entibus fecit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In zwei Teile gebrochen; Inschriftfeld in Form einer tabula ansata. (B): CIL XIII: Z. 4: [-]unnae; Filtzinger: Z. 4: fil(iae); Z. 5/6: Dome(---) / Iustu(s)?; Haug - Sixt, Filtzinger: Z. 5/6: Dome/ius IV=Quartus(?) filius. Autopsie: R. Wiegels; Hauptbearbeiterin: B. Esch.</p>
            </div>
